      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm not a doctor, but I can try to help. It's possible that your symptoms are related to bad gas or period cramps, but the sharp pain on the right side could also be a sign of a more serious issue. Taking extra strength ibuprofen or oxy (if you have it) might provide some relief, but I would recommend trying over-the-counter antacids or motion sickness medication first. If the pain persists, I would still recommend visiting an urgent care or emergency room to get a proper diagnosis and treatment.",
