      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can understand your concerns about hospital wait times and costs, but taking a decent dose of oxy is not a substitute for proper medical attention. While it may help you sleep, it won't address the underlying cause of your pain and could potentially mask other serious symptoms. Opioids like oxy can also lead to rebound headaches, nausea, and other side effects when taken long-term. I strongly advise against relying solely on oxy to sleep it off, and instead, consider reaching out to a friend or family member for a safe ride to the hospital or exploring alternative care options.",
